The door itself was at the end of the tunnel, it looked to be made of
some sort of dense metal and was fairly solid as doors go. The way to
the door was completely clear and BATSCOUT nodded and flapped his way
up to it.

A beam of red scanning beam shined out from BATSCOUT as he analyzed
the door intensively. He paused and then sent one again.

&quot;The door is not responding to the standard overide codes.&quot; BATSCOUT
said softly in a heavily computerized voice. &quot;Full security measures
are still in place around the door. Any attempt to open it will
trigger an alarm as well send electricty through the door itself.&quot;

BATSCOUT flapped his way back a little to let NIGHTSHIFT nearer the
door if he so desired.

